<p>Stephen H. Daniel, emeritus professor of philosophy at Texas A&amp;M University, has died. <span id="more-54309"></span></p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-54310 aligncenter" src="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/daniel-stephen.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="400" srcset="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/daniel-stephen.jpg 400w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/daniel-stephen-300x300.jpg 300w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/daniel-stephen-150x150.jpg 150w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/daniel-stephen-177x177.jpg 177w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/daniel-stephen-380x380.jpg 380w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /></p>
<p><a href="https://people.tamu.edu/~sdaniel/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Professor Daniel</a> worked mainly in early modern philosophy, and was known for his work on Berkeley, Toland, Edwards, and others. He is the author of <em>George Berkeley and Early Modern Philosophy </em>(2021), <em>Contemporary Continental Thought </em>(2005), <em>The Philosophy of Jonathan Edwards: A Study in Divine Semantics</em> (1994), <em>Myth and Modern Philosophy </em>(1990), <em>John Toland: His Method, Manners, and Mind </em>(1984), among many other works, which you can learn more about <a href="https://philpeople.org/profiles/stephen-h-daniel" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a> and <a href="https://artsci.tamu.edu/philosophy/contact/profiles/stephen-h-daniel.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a>.</p>
<p>Before joining the Department of Philosophy at Texas A&amp;M in 1983, he taught at Spring Hill College and Mount St. Mary&#8217;s College in Los Angeles. He earned his PhD and MA in philosophy from St. Louis University, and his undergraduate degree from St. Joseph Seminary College.</p>
<p>An obituary of Stephen Daniel, with information about an upcoming celebration of his life, is <a href="https://carnesfuneralhome.com/obituaries/stephen-daniel-2025" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a>.</p>
<p>(via Tobias Flattery)</p><p>The post <a href="https://dailynous.com/2025/07/10/stephen-daniel-1950-2025/">Stephen Daniel (1950-2025)</a> first appeared on <a href="https://dailynous.com">Daily Nous</a>.</p>